<h1>Horizontal Rules</h1>
<p>In HTML, the horizontal rule element (<code>&lt;hr&gt;</code>) represents a paragraph-level thematic break. BaseWeb provides some very basic and subtle styles for this element along with a few stylistic class modifiers.</p>

<pre class="language-markup"><code>&lt;hr&gt;</code></pre>

<div class="demo">
  <hr>
</div>

<section class="subsection subsection-classes has-inner-subsection">
<div class="inner-subsection">
  <h1>Horizontal Rule Classes</h1>
  <p class="text-lead">These are the available classes for modifying the look of your horizontal rule.</p>
</div>
<ul class="docs-list">
  
  <li>
    <h2>.hr-dotted</h2>
    <p>Uses the dotted border style property to created a dotted rule.</p>
    <pre class="language-markup"><code>&lt;hr class=&quot;hr-dotted&quot;&gt;</code></pre>
    <div class="demo">
      <hr class="hr-dotted">
    </div>
  </li>
  
  <li>
    <h2>.hr-dashed</h2>
    <p>Uses the dashed border style property to created a dashed rule.</p>
    <pre class="language-markup"><code>&lt;hr class=&quot;hr-dashed&quot;&gt;</code></pre>
    <div class="demo">
      <hr class="hr-dashed">
    </div>
  </li>
  
  <li>
    <h2>.hr-double</h2>
    <p>Uses the double border style property to created a double bordered rule.</p>
    <pre class="language-markup"><code>&lt;hr class=&quot;hr-double&quot;&gt;</code></pre>
    <div class="demo">
      <hr class="hr-double">
    </div>
  </li>
  
</ul>
</section>
